<div id="review_913904602" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/913904602" />
    <a title="Tonya" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5717909-tonya"><img alt="Tonya" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1513736337p2/5717909.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/913904602?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tonya" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tonya" href="/user/show/5717909-tonya">Tonya</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5717909-tonya?shelf=2014-personal-challenge">2014-personal-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5717909-tonya?shelf=adult-contemporary">adult-contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5717909-tonya?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5717909-tonya?shelf=read-and-review">read-and-review</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer913904602" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4299438318825604969">Come Find Me was an absolute joy to read, once I picked it up it was very hard to put down. Jessica and Mark both grew up in military families, moving with their families every two years. They were together when they were born, even sharing the same crib when Mark was vital signs were failing. They were together again at the age of 16 and it was young love for 6 blissful weeks, when Mark moved again and shortly thereafter both of their fathers were killed in the Iraqi war. Neither one was aware </span>
  <span id="freeText4299438318825604969" style="display:none">Come Find Me was an absolute joy to read, once I picked it up it was very hard to put down. Jessica and Mark both grew up in military families, moving with their families every two years. They were together when they were born, even sharing the same crib when Mark was vital signs were failing. They were together again at the age of 16 and it was young love for 6 blissful weeks, when Mark moved again and shortly thereafter both of their fathers were killed in the Iraqi war. Neither one was aware of what the other was going through, and each thought the other had pulled away and forgot them. Flash forward 10 years and Jessica is helping care for her sister's children and engaged to Blake, a seemingly safe (yet slimy) man. Mark has made a promise to his mother to look up Jessica before he continues on his solitary travels. Will they be able to reconnect, or has too much time passed? <br />It was easy to get caught up into the storyline, the overwhelming feeling I had was one of hope and happiness, even though life dealt the main characters hard blows, they had faith and love. There are some love scenes that are "steamy" (blush worthy, but very tasteful!). I would recommend this novel to anyone that loves a great romance. I'm really looking forward to reading more by this author!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4299438318825604969" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


